<br>
I sit corrected.  The books of the Maccabees are not of NT but of OT times.  However that are not apart of the OT in the KJV, and other Bibles, because they were not considered to be part of the Old Testament by the Jews, themselves.<br>
<br>
As to the canonicity of the New Testament books, they were established by Peter and John.  I am not about to reproduce two chapters of a book, Jeff, sorry about that.  However, if you wish to research it yourself the writings of Eusibius, the early Christian historian/librarian, would be helpful.  He was instrumental in maintaining and distributing copies of the original texts until they were put into codex form.  <br>
<br>
There are still copies of the oringinal writings, in Greek, which are are the basis for all the New Testament translations extant today.  <br>
<br>
You have your head in the sand, Jeff, if you think all the OT prophecies have been fulfilled.  They have not!<br>
-------<br>
Thank you, Esdras, for your informative post on the matter of UN sanctions and such.  It is appreciated.<br>
<br>
I think we could see the covenant that is to be confirmed for seven years come about as a result of the current peace initiative, even if the Palestian terror militias swear they will not stop until Israel is driven into the sea.<br>
<br>
That, to my mind, is why Luke 21:36 is of extreme importance for believers today.  We can see these things beginning to come to pass.<br>
<br>
God Bless you.  Charlie Baker. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bsparrowshearth.showUserPublicProfile?gid=esdras>esdras</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator<br>Sir Esdras, Brewmeister <br>of the Great White North</span><br>  Posts: 156<br> <font color=#B87333>(6/6/03 8:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fsparrowshearthfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=16.topic&index=25>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www3.sympatico.ca/gsmorgan/images/ADPY005.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: A Question to Jeff and Esdras.</span><hr size=1> Hi Charles:<br>
<br>
You may want to check out the history of the King James Version of the Bible.  The original version first printed in 1611 included the following Table of Contents:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.geocities.com/Athens/Rhodes/1967/content.htm" target="top">KJV 1611 Table of Contents</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
