If you should have evidence that it was so, from Eusibius writings, that is, it would help if you were to identify in which of them the evidence appears.<br>
<br>
I think subsequent disputes between the Greek Catholic Church and the Roman Catholic Church led to many changes.  Changes that, for the most part, were motivated by the biases of the leaders of the two opposing factions.  Each group had their own biases, just as your leaders are biased against Israel and you follow their dictates.<br>
<br>
From Jeff:<br>
&quot;The Canon of the New Testament was not firmed up until around 397 AD with the Council of Carthage.&quot;<br>
<br>
From Charlie:<br>
There were complete copies of the New Testament in circulation before that time, Jeff, that were arranged canonically but Constantine wanted to rearrange the order of the books, and did change some to the original texts,  to suit his 'state church' concept.  A Church that would be under the dictates of the State.  The present day Vatican is a church state, completely autonomous from other states.<br>
<br>
The Roman Church leaders wanted it one way, the Greek Church leaders wanted it another way, and the true canon was lost in the shuffle because those who were following usin the New Testament as originally written in the order in which they were arranged, were loving their neighbors as themselves rather than trying to make a name for themselves.<br>
<br>
Your leaders are trying to make a name for themselves, today.  They are not alone, every denomination is <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>led by</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> men who are driven by a desire to dictate.<br>
<br>
The Bible tells us, in Romans 10:9,<br>
<br>
&quot;If thou shalt confess with thy mouth the Lord Jesus, and shalt believe in thine heart that God hath raised him from the dead, thou shalt be saved.&quot;<br>
<br>
Only God knows what anyone believes in their heart, Jeff!  Believers are not to forsake the gathering of themselves together to worship the Lord but they are not required to do is as part of any particular church.<br>
<br>
Jesus said, where two or three are gathered together in my name I am in the midst of them.  That is what counts!!!<br>
<br>
Just my thoughts.<br>
<br>
God Bless you.  Charlie Baker. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bsparrowshearth.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jeffthefinn>jeffthefinn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://webpages.charter.net/nilus/finnbutton.GIF" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered Member</span><br>  Posts: 26<br> <font color=#B87333>(6/7/03 10:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fsparrowshearthfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=16.topic&index=31>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://webpages.charter.net/nilus/jfinn.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: A Question to Jeff and Esdras.</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Your leaders are trying to make a name for themselves, today. They are not alone, every denomination is led by men who are driven by a desire to dictate.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
