P.S.  Ignatius of Antioch may have been ordained by the Apostle John, appointed, not doubt, as a bishop.  I do not know, Jeff.  However, that does not put all of what Ignatius wrote on a par with what Holy Men of God wrote, as they were moved by the Holy Ghost.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#DEB887><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bsparrowshearth.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jeffthefinn>jeffthefinn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://webpages.charter.net/nilus/finnbutton.GIF" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered Member</span><br>  Posts: 28<br> <font color=#B87333>(6/8/03 3:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fsparrowshearthfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=16.topic&index=36>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://webpages.charter.net/nilus/jfinn.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: A Question to Jeff and Esdras.</span><hr size=1> Where was that teaching before John Nelson Darby?  And how is it that it came on the scene so late.?<br>
7 Churches meant one church in one city, not 7 sects but these churches were all in communion with the Apostles so it was one Church.  Have you ever thought about what Our Lord was praying for in John 17?  Was he praying for thousands of sects?<br>
If you are saying that St Igantius did not know what he was talking about then how on earth would anyone believe John Nelson Darby's new Gospel which is totally at odds with anything that came before.  It is not the faith once delivered to the saints.  St Ignatius was during the New Testament so he knew what the Apostle's taught.<br>
But it was folks like St Ignatius that preserved for you the New Testament and therefore he was inspired to pick the right tradition.<br>
Jeff the Finn <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://webpages.charter.net/nilus" target="top">Nilus</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bsparrowshearth.showUserPublicProfile?gid=charlesbaker>Charles Baker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered Member</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#B87333>(6/9/03 8:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fsparrowshearthfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=16.topic&index=37>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: A Question to Jeff and Esdras.</span><hr size=1> Dear Jeff:<br>
<br>
I am not familiar with the writings of Darby nor with those of Ignanius of Antioch.  I have quite enough occupy my mind with in what is written in the Bible.<br>
<br>
What is written, there, Jeff, in the Bible, considered in the context of the times, and without a prejudice against Israel, has been my guide.<br>
